  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into <strong>chips</strong>, then add to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, your<strong> ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the chips are golden and starting to crisp – these are your <strong>smoky chips</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643798516440-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643798516440-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643798516440-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643798516440-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643798516440-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span><strong> butter</strong> from the fridge to warm up for later</p><p>Cut a piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> approx. the size of an A4 sheet of paper</p><p>Lay <strong>half</strong> your <strong>garlic cloves </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) (skins on) in the middle of the foil, then add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, a small splash of <strong>water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643798525532-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643798525532-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643798525532-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643798525532-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643798525532-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Scrunch the edges of the tin foil together around the garlic to form a sealed parcel</p><p>Add the <strong>garlic parcel</strong> to a separate tray and put the tray in the oven for 15 min or until the garlic is soft</p><p>Once soft, carefully remove the skins from the <strong>roasted garlic </strong>(they will be hot!),<strong> </strong>mash with a fork and set aside</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1643798543415-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1643798543415-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1643798543415-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
